			<description><![CDATA[<p>
We&#39;re looking for a fantastic <strong>Group Director</strong> candidate to serve as the leader for a specific set of account teams internally, acting as a liaison between Account leads and the Leadership team, and ultimately responsible for the health and success of the account.</p>
<p>
<strong>Who are you?</strong><br />
<br />
You are an agency, digital, and business-world veteran with leadership, management, communication, and high-level relationship skills in spades.</p>
<p>
<strong>The task at hand:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Deliver senior-level counsel externally, manage team leaders internally, and contribute to the growth and general health of a series of accounts.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Responsible for contributing to the the growth and stability of VM as a whole; focused on the big picture and owning forward-thinking planning at a master brand level and within the VM client portfolio as a whole.</li>
<li>
Assignments within internal initiatives, business development activities and the expansion of services and regions as dictated by the Leadership team will account for half of the Group Director&rsquo;s capacity.</li>
<li>
Empowered to make business decisions in the best interests of the client and VM, with the ability to supercede decisions made at the Account lead level.</li>
<li>
Responsible for providing business-level updates and requesting input from the Leadership team when necessary.</li>
<li>
Report in to the Leadership team, and manage the Account leads on their accounts, and as a result have ultimate responsibility for all staff assigned to their teams.</li>
<li>
Collaborate proactively with the leaders of other departments, Creative and Strategy, to improve client deliverables, process, and output.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The ideal candidate has:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A Bachelor&#39;s degree and 10-12 years of experience working within the digital and agency space</li>
<li>
Seriously advanced written and spoken communication skills</li>
<li>
Deep understanding and proven expertise in the social space and how it relates to branding and the wider marketing mix for Fortune 500 brands</li>
<li>
Experience managing and growing large teams of at least 20-25 people</li>
<li>
Passion for mentoring, teaching, and developing talent within staff</li>
<li>
Impeccable social and relationship-building skills and the ability to command a room of C-suite executives</li>
<li>
A magnetic personality and broad set of interests that brings fresh air and an added dimension to our company culture</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
