			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Location: New York, NY&nbsp; Type:&nbsp; Full Time Min. Experience: Junior-Mid Level</p>
<p>
The Micro-Content Producer specializes in bridging the gap, through social content, between a brand and its community.<br />
Who are you?</p>
<p>
You&rsquo;re an ultimate team player who will create value in any situation. You understand brand voice and have a passion for storytelling on every platform.&nbsp; You can recognize trends, and use data to make recommendations and optimize your content.&nbsp; You&rsquo;re highly observant and write because you love to.&nbsp; You can execute quickly and manage your time well. You&rsquo;re aware of your strengths and your weaknesses.&nbsp; You&rsquo;re cool in the face of a challenge.&nbsp; You&rsquo;re &ldquo;good at the internet.&rdquo;</p>
<p>
<strong>The task at hand:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll work within a dynamic team structure with several creative leads to write and develop content that honors the brand while standing out from the noise</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll have a mastery of industry best practices and the ability to design content appropriate for each social platform, as well as be willing to learn and articulate the unique VaynerMedia POV on each</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll care more about concepting, writing, developing, and putting the team in the best position to present our ideas than you do about getting credit for the work</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;re expected to be as much of a friendly teacher as a proficient doer when working community managers and multi-disciplinary team around you</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll have strong storytelling skills, a mastery of grammar and the English language, and a strategic mind that can make creative decisions based on data</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll invest in popular culture and digital spaces to bring seemingly unrelated content ideas and concepts to bear</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The Ideal Candidate has:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A Bachelor&rsquo;s degree and 1-3 years of experience copywriting, developing, and creating for digital/social strategies + campaigns</li>
<li>
Strong conceptual and brainstorming skills</li>
<li>
The ability to follow direction and take constructive criticism</li>
<li>
An aptitude for time management, organization, and communication</li>
<li>
The ability to write concisely and with a strong voice, without typo or delay and with general editorial sensibilities</li>
<li>
The ability to effectively collaborate with various teams, providing the most useful guidance in an enthusiastic and inspiring manner</li>
<li>
A sparkling personality that will mesh well with the existing VaynerMedia family and a smile on their face a majority of the time</li>
<li>
An insatiable curiosity and knowledge about all things social, web, and mobile</li>
<li>
A deep love and respect for communities and the power that can be housed within them supplemented by a commitment to listen and adapt as they change</li>
<li>
Passion for the things you do outside of work-we love people who can bring their own interests into the mix</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Please submit a digital portfolio with resume submissions.</p>
